/****** Object:  View [dbo].[VwPendingPlanPurchase]    Script Date: 3/9/2021 10:38:30 AM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE VIEW [dbo].[VwPendingPlanPurchase]
AS
	SELECT
	a.Name AS [Name STR]
	,a.MobileNo AS [Mobile STR]
	,a.EmailId AS [Email STR]
	,b.GroupName AS [Group STR]
	,c.SubGroupName AS [Sub Group STR]
	,a.Organisation AS [Organisation STR]
	,a.Usertype AS [Type STR]
	,a.Address AS [Address STR]
	FROM m_registered a
	JOIN m_group b ON a.GroupId = b.Id
	JOIN m_subgroup c ON a.SubGroupId = c.SubGroupId
	WHERE a.Status = 1 AND a.Usertype = 'EXTERNAL' AND a.RegisteredId NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT(UserID) FROM m_user_plan WHERE Status = 1)
GO
/****** Object:  View [dbo].[VwPlanWiseUsers]    Script Date: 3/9/2021 10:38:30 AM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE VIEW [dbo].[VwPlanWiseUsers]
AS

	SELECT a.Name AS [Name STR]
	,a.MobileNo AS [Mobile STR]
	,a.EmailId AS [Email STR]
	,b.GroupName AS [Group STR]
	,c.SubGroupName AS [Sub Group STR]
	,a.Organisation AS [Organisation STR]
	,a.Usertype AS [Type STR]
	,a.Address AS [Address STR]
	,e.PlanName AS [Plan STR]
	,e.ActualPrice AS [PlanPrice STR]
	,e.Validity AS [Validity INT]
	FROM m_user_plan d 
	JOIN m_registered a ON d.UserId = a.RegisteredId
	JOIN m_group b ON a.GroupId = b.Id
	JOIN m_subgroup c ON a.SubGroupId = c.SubGroupId
	JOIN m_plan e ON d.PlanId = e.PlanId
	WHERE a.Status = 1
GO
/****** Object:  View [dbo].[VwRegistrations]    Script Date: 3/9/2021 10:38:30 AM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE VIEW [dbo].[VwRegistrations]
AS
	SELECT
	a.Name AS [Name STR]
	,a.MobileNo AS [Mobile STR]
	,a.EmailId AS [Email STR]
	,b.GroupName AS [Group STR]
	,c.SubGroupName AS [Sub Group STR]
	,a.Organisation AS [Organisation STR]
	,a.Usertype AS [Type STR]
	,a.Address AS [Address STR]
	FROM m_registered a 
	JOIN m_group b ON a.GroupId = b.Id
	JOIN m_subgroup c ON a.SubGroupId = c.SubGroupId
	WHERE a.Status = 1
GO
/****** Object:  View [dbo].[VwResources]    Script Date: 3/9/2021 10:38:30 AM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE VIEW [dbo].[VwResources]
AS
	SELECT
	b.HostName AS [HostName STR],
	b.IPAddress AS [IP STR],
	b.FQDN AS [FQDN STR],
	c.Name AS [Asset STR],
	a.Qty AS [Qty STR],
	a.UnallocatedQty AS [RemainingQty STR],
	d.Name AS [Unit STR]	
	FROM m_server_detail a
	JOIN m_server b ON a.ServerId = b.ServerId
	JOIN m_asset c ON a.AssetId = c.AssetId
	JOIN m_unit d ON a.UnitId = d.UnitId
	WHERE a.Status = 1 and b.Status = 1
GO
/****** Object:  View [dbo].[VwScripts]    Script Date: 3/9/2021 10:38:30 AM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE VIEW [dbo].[VwScripts]
AS
	SELECT 
	b.CategoryName AS [Category STR],
	a.Name AS [ScriptName STR],
	a.Description AS [Description STR],
	a.ParamCount AS [Para INT],
	ISNULL(x.KeyName,'') AS [KeyName STR]
	FROM m_script a
	JOIN m_category b ON a.CategoryId = b.CategoryId
	LEFT OUTER JOIN 
	(
		SELECT  ScriptId
       ,STUFF((SELECT ', ' + CAST(KeyDisplayName AS VARCHAR(10)) [text()]
         FROM m_script_key 
         WHERE ScriptId = t.ScriptId
         FOR XML PATH(''), TYPE)
        .value('.','NVARCHAR(MAX)'),1,2,' ') KeyName
		FROM m_script_key t
		GROUP BY ScriptId
	) x ON x.ScriptId = a.ScriptId
	WHERE a.Status = 1
GO

#===================================Setting up OS User on Master node ======================
setting_up_ubuntu_user()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Setting up ububtu user - Started"
echo " "

sudo useradd -p $(openssl passwd -1 $password) -m $username
echo "user created"

#user=$(sudo useradd -m -d /home/$username -s /bin/bash -c "$displayname " $username 2&gt;&1)
#echo "$user"
#echo admin123 | sudo -S echo -e  "$password\n$password\n" |passwd $username
#echo "password changed"
u_confirm="$(sudo id $username)"
echo "$username - UID & GID:"
echo $u_confirm

user_len=${#username}
echo $user_len
user_new=$(echo $u_confirm |awk ''{ print substr($0,10,$user_len)}'')
echo $user_new
user_test=0
if [ "$user_new" == "$username" ] ;
then
user_test=1
fi
echo "User Creation Test = $user_test"

}

#==============================Setting up Permissions on USER directory============================

setting_up_file_permissions()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting File Permission on user home directory - Started"
echo " "
sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username
sudo chmod -R 755 /home/$username
echo "Permissions on Home Directory:"
echo " "
cd /home
user_hm=$(sudo ls $username -l)
echo $user_hm
echo " "


hmdir_test=0
user_hmdir=$(echo user_hm | grep $username |awk ''{print $1}'')
if [ $user_hmdir == "drwxr-xr-x" ];
then
hmdir_test=1
fi
echo "Home Directory Test = $hmdir_test" 
}


#=====================================Command to create users on Compute Nodes====================================

nodeuser_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Command to create user on compute node section - Started"
echo " "

userid=$(sudo id $username)
user_id=$(echo $userid | awk ''{print substr($0,5,4)}'')
echo "UID of $username - $user_id"
nodeuser="sudo useradd -u $user_id -m -d /userdata/$username -s /bin/bash -c \"$displayname\" $username"
echo "Command for Compute nodes:"
echo $nodeuser
echo " "
}


#-m  Craeting home directory as /$HOME/$username
#-d  Giving a different path to home directory
#-s  To specify a default shell
#-c  To  provide a comment
#sudo useradd -m -d /opt/username username
#sudo useradd -u 1500 username
#sudo useradd -g users username

#========================================Kubernetes Credential Setup======================================================================

credential_creation()
 {

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Credential Setup - Started"
echo " "

        cd $HOME/.certs

        mkdir $username
echo "Namespace Creation"
        sudo kubectl create namespace $username
        user_ns=$(sudo kubectl  get namespace $username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "User Namespace:"
        echo "$user_ns"
        echo " "
echo "Key Generation"
        user_key=$(sudo openssl genrsa -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2048 2&lt;&1)
        echo "$user_key"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Signing Request Generation"
        user_csr=$(sudo openssl req -new -key $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -subj /CN=$username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_csr"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Creation & Signing"
        user_cert=$(sudo openssl x509 -req -in $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -CA /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.crt -CAkey /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt -days $validity 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_cert"
        echo " "
echo "Ubuntu User Account \"$username\" mapping with generated certificate & key"
        user_cred_set=$(sudo kubectl config set-credentials $username --client-certificate=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt --client-key=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2&gt;&1)
        user_cred_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |grep -A50 users:|grep -A0 $username)
        echo "$user_cred_set"
        echo "$username Mappings:"
        echo "$user_cred_verify"
        echo " "
echo "Context setup for  $username : "
        user_context=$(sudo kubectl config set-context $username --cluster=kubernetes --namespace=$username --user=$username 2&gt;&1)
        user_context_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |awk ''/context:/,/current-context:/''|grep -B4 "name: $username")
        echo "$user_context"
        echo "$username Context:"
        echo "$user_context_verify"
        echo "Files Created during the operation:"

cd $username
dir

}


#=====================================Kubernetes Roles Creation======================================================================


roles_creation()

{

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd  $HOME/.RBAC
mkdir $username
cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: OnlyJobs
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods","pods/log"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch"]
- apiGroups: ["batch","extensions"]
  resources: ["jobs"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch","create","update","patch","delete"]
EOF




cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: owner
rules:
- apiGroups: ["*"]
  resources: ["*"]
  verbs: ["*"]
EOF


cd $HOME/.RBAC/$username

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml

echo "Roles Created :"
user_role1=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep owner)
user_role2=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep OnlyJobs)
echo "User Role 1 - $user_role1"
echo "User Role 2 - $user_role2"

echo "Roles .yaml file are generated during operations:"
dir
}

#===================================Kubernetes Role Bindings Creation===========================================================

rolebinding_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role Binding creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-RoleBinding.yaml
kind: RoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: $username
  namespace: $username
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: $username
  apiGroup: ""
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: owner
  apiGroup: ""

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/$username-RoleBinding.yaml
echo "Role Binding Operation:"
user_rolebinding=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings   --all-namespaces    -o custom-columns=''KIND:kind,NAMESPACE:metadata.namespace,NAME:metadata.name,SERVICE_ACCOUNTS:subjects[?(@.kind=="ServiceAccount")].name''|grep "$username" 2&gt;&1)
echo "$user_rolebinding"

echo "Role binding file generated during operation"
dir
}

#==================================User Configuration File Generation===============================

create_config_file()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== User Configuration file Generation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd /etc/kubernetes/

sudo sed -n ''1,9 p'' admin.conf &gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config

cat &lt;&lt;EOT &gt;&gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config
    namespace: $username
    user: $username
  name: $username
current-context: $username
kind: Config
preferences: {}
users:
- name: $username
  user:
    client-certificate: $username.crt
    client-key: $username.key
EOT

echo " Config File Generated"
user_config_file=$(cat $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config)
echo "$user_config_file"



}



#====================================================Authentication Files - Provisioning to User=========-======

copy_authentication_files()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Authentication Files - Provisioning to User Setup - Started"
echo " "
		sudo chmod -R 755 /home/$username
        cd /
        cd /home/$username
        pwd
        sudo mkdir .kube
        sudo cp $HOME/.certs/$username/* /home/$username/.kube
        sudo rm /home/$username/.kube/$username.csr
        sudo cp /home/$username/.kube/$username.config /home/$username/.kube/config
        sudo cp /home/jarvis/pod_creation.sh .
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/*
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/.kube
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/.kube/*
        cd .kube
        ls -a
echo "Authentication File Transfered:"

}



#========================================Setting Kube Config File=====================================



set_kubeconfig()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Kube Config File Setup - Started"
echo " "

echo "sudo export KUBECONFIG=/home/$username/.k8s-authentication/$username.config" &gt;&gt; /home/$username/.bashrc

echo "Kube Config  file set"

}


#=====================================Setting Resource quota===========================================

set_quota()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting Resource Quota Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: compute-resource
spec:
  hard:
    requests.nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
EOF

echo "Quota has been set"

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl create -f $HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml --namespace=$username

user_quota=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl describe namespace $username)
echo "$user_quota"
}

#echo "$user"
#echo admin123 | sudo -S echo -e  "$password\n$password\n" |passwd $username
#echo "password changed"
u_confirm="$(sudo id $username)"
echo "$username - UID & GID:"
echo $u_confirm

}

#==============================Setting up Permissions on USER directory============================

setting_up_file_permissions()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting File Permission on user home directory - Started"
echo " "
sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username
sudo chmod -R 755 /home/$username
echo "Permissions on Home Directory:"
echo " "
cd /home
user_hm=$(sudo ls $username -l)
echo $user_hm
echo " "
}


#=====================================Command to create users on Compute Nodes====================================

nodeuser_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Command to create user on compute node section - Started"
echo " "

userid=$(sudo id $username)
user_id=$(echo $userid | awk ''{print substr($0,5,4)}'')
echo "UID of $username - $user_id"
nodeuser="sudo useradd -u $user_id -m -d /userdata/$username -s /bin/bash -c \"$displayname\" $username"
echo "Command for Compute nodes:"
echo $nodeuser
echo " "
}


#-m  Craeting home directory as /$HOME/$username
#-d  Giving a different path to home directory
#-s  To specify a default shell
#-c  To  provide a comment
#sudo useradd -m -d /opt/username username

#========================================Kubernetes Credential Setup======================================================================

credential_creation()
 {

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Credential Setup - Started"
echo " "

        cd $HOME/.certs

        mkdir $username
echo "Namespace Creation"
        sudo kubectl create namespace $username
        user_ns=$(sudo kubectl  get namespace $username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "User Namespace:"
        echo "$user_ns"
        echo " "
echo "Key Generation"
        user_key=$(sudo openssl genrsa -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2048 2&lt;&1)
        echo "$user_key"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Signing Request Generation"
        user_csr=$(sudo openssl req -new -key $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -subj /CN=$username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_csr"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Creation & Signing"
        user_cert=$(sudo openssl x509 -req -in $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -CA /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.crt -CAkey /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt -days $validity 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_cert"
        echo " "
echo "Ubuntu User Account \"$username\" mapping with generated certificate & key"
        user_cred_set=$(sudo kubectl config set-credentials $username --client-certificate=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt --client-key=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2&gt;&1)
        user_cred_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |grep -A50 users:|grep -A0 $username)
        echo "$user_cred_set"
        echo "$username Mappings:"
        echo "$user_cred_verify"
        echo " "
echo "Context setup for  $username : "
        user_context=$(sudo kubectl config set-context $username --cluster=kubernetes --namespace=$username --user=$username 2&gt;&1)
        user_context_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |awk ''/context:/,/current-context:/''|grep -B4 "name: $username")
        echo "$user_context"
        echo "$username Context:"
        echo "$user_context_verify"
        echo "Files Created during the operation:"

cd $username
dir

}


#=====================================Kubernetes Roles Creation======================================================================


roles_creation()

{

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd  $HOME/.RBAC
mkdir $username
cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: OnlyJobs
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods","pods/log"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch"]
- apiGroups: ["batch","extensions"]
  resources: ["jobs"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch","create","update","patch","delete"]
EOF




cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: owner
rules:
- apiGroups: ["*"]
  resources: ["*"]
  verbs: ["*"]
EOF


cd $HOME/.RBAC/$username

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml

echo "Roles Created :"
user_role1=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep owner)
user_role2=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep OnlyJobs)
echo "User Role 1 - $user_role1"
echo "User Role 2 - $user_role2"

echo "Roles .yaml file are generated during operations:"
dir
}

#===================================Kubernetes Role Bindings Creation===========================================================

rolebinding_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role Binding creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-RoleBinding.yaml
kind: RoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: $username
  namespace: $username
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: $username
  apiGroup: ""
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: owner
  apiGroup: ""

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/$username-RoleBinding.yaml
echo "Role Binding Operation:"
user_rolebinding=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings   --all-namespaces    -o custom-columns=''KIND:kind,NAMESPACE:metadata.namespace,NAME:metadata.name,SERVICE_ACCOUNTS:subjects[?(@.kind=="ServiceAccount")].name''|grep "$username" 2&gt;&1)
echo "$user_rolebinding"

echo "Role binding file generated during operation"
dir
}

#==================================User Configuration File Generation===============================

create_config_file()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== User Configuration file Generation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd /etc/kubernetes/

sudo sed -n ''1,9 p'' admin.conf &gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config

cat &lt;&lt;EOT &gt;&gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config
    namespace: $username
    user: $username
  name: $username
current-context: $username
kind: Config
preferences: {}
users:
- name: $username
  user:
    client-certificate: $username.crt
    client-key: $username.key
EOT

echo " Config File Generated"
user_config_file=$(cat $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config)
echo "$user_config_file"



}



#====================================================Authentication Files - Provisioning to User=========-======

copy_authentication_files()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Authentication Files - Provisioning to User Setup - Started"
echo " "
		sudo chmod -R 755 /home/$username
        cd /
        cd /home/$username
        pwd
        sudo mkdir .kube
        sudo cp $HOME/.certs/$username/* /home/$username/.kube
        sudo rm /home/$username/.kube/$username.csr
        sudo cp /home/$username/.kube/$username.config /home/$username/.kube/config
        sudo cp /home/jarvis/pod_creation.sh .
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/*
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/.kube
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/.kube/*
        cd .kube
        ls -a
echo "Authentication File Transfered:"

}

}


#=====================================Setting Resource quota===========================================

set_quota()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting Resource Quota Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: compute-resource
spec:
  hard:
    requests.nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
EOF

echo "Quota has been set"

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl create -f $HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml --namespace=$username

user_quota=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl describe namespace $username)
echo "$user_quota"
}

setting_up_ubuntu_user()
{

echo " "

echo $user_new
user_test=0
if [ "$user_new" == "$username" ] ;
then
user_test=1
fi
echo "User Creation Test = $user_test"

}

credential_creation()
 {

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Credential Setup - Started"
echo " "

        cd $HOME/.certs

        mkdir $username
echo "Namespace Creation"
        sudo kubectl create namespace $username
        user_ns=$(sudo kubectl  get namespace $username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "User Namespace:"
        echo "$user_ns"
        echo " "
echo "Key Generation"
        user_key=$(sudo openssl genrsa -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2048 2&lt;&1)
        echo "$user_key"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Signing Request Generation"
        user_csr=$(sudo openssl req -new -key $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -subj /CN=$username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_csr"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Creation & Signing"
        user_cert=$(sudo openssl x509 -req -in $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -CA /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.crt -CAkey /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt -days $validity 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_cert"
        echo " "
echo "Ubuntu User Account \"$username\" mapping with generated certificate & key"
        user_cred_set=$(sudo kubectl config set-credentials $username --client-certificate=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt --client-key=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2&gt;&1)
        user_cred_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |grep -A50 users:|grep -A0 $username)
        echo "$user_cred_set"
        echo "$username Mappings:"
        echo "$user_cred_verify"
        echo " "
echo "Context setup for  $username : "
        user_context=$(sudo kubectl config set-context $username --cluster=kubernetes --namespace=$username --user=$username 2&gt;&1)
        user_context_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |awk ''/context:/,/current-context:/''|grep -B4 "name: $username")
        echo "$user_context"
        echo "$username Context:"
        echo "$user_context_verify"
        echo "Files Created during the operation:"

cd $username
dir

}

echo $svc_nodeport

echo $pod_ip_link

host_ip_link="$(echo "http://$host_ip:$svc_nodeport/?token=$jup_token")"

if [ "$token_len" = 48 ];

 then

        status="Failed"

# Create $HOME/.certs

#=========================================Variable Declarations=============================

setting_up_ubuntu_user()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Setting up ububtu user - Started"
echo " "

sudo useradd -p $(openssl passwd -1 $password) -m $username
echo "user created"

#user=$(sudo useradd -m -d /home/$username -s /bin/bash -c "$displayname " $username 2&gt;&1)
#echo "$user"
#echo admin123 | sudo -S echo -e  "$password\n$password\n" |passwd $username
#echo "password changed"
u_confirm="$(sudo id $username)"
echo "$username - UID & GID:"
echo $u_confirm

user_len=${#username}
echo $user_len
user_new=$(echo $u_confirm |awk ''{ print substr($0,10,$user_len)}'')
echo $user_new
user_test=0
if [ "$user_new" == "$username" ] ;
then
user_test=1
fi
echo "User Creation Test = $user_test"

}

#==============================Setting up Permissions on USER directory============================

setting_up_file_permissions()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting File Permission on user home directory - Started"
echo " "
sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username
sudo chmod -R 755 /home/$username
echo "Permissions on Home Directory:"
echo " "
cd /home
user_hm=$(sudo ls $username -l)
echo $user_hm
echo " "


hmdir_test=0
user_hmdir=$(echo user_hm | grep $username |awk ''{print $1}'')
if [ "$user_hmdir" == "drwxr-xr-x" ];
then
hmdir_test=1
fi
echo "Home Directory Test = $hmdir_test" 
}


#=====================================Command to create users on Compute Nodes====================================

nodeuser_creation()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Command to create user on compute node section - Started"
echo " "

userid=$(sudo id $username)
user_id=$(echo $userid | awk ''{print substr($0,5,4)}'')
echo "UID of $username - $user_id"
nodeuser="sudo useradd -u $user_id -m -d /userdata/$username -s /bin/bash -c \"$displayname\" $username"
echo "Command for Compute nodes:"
echo $nodeuser
echo "[{\"computenodecommand\":\"$nodeuser\"}]"
}


#-m  Craeting home directory as /$HOME/$username
#-d  Giving a different path to home directory
#-s  To specify a default shell
#-c  To  provide a comment
#sudo useradd -m -d /opt/username username
#sudo useradd -u 1500 username
#sudo useradd -g users username

#========================================Kubernetes Credential Setup======================================================================

credential_creation()
 {

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Credential Setup - Started"
echo " "

        cd $HOME/.certs

        mkdir $username
echo "Namespace Creation"
        sudo kubectl create namespace $username
        user_ns=$(sudo kubectl  get namespace $username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "User Namespace:"
        echo "$user_ns"
        echo " "
echo "Key Generation"
        user_key=$(sudo openssl genrsa -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2048 2&lt;&1)
        echo "$user_key"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Signing Request Generation"
        user_csr=$(sudo openssl req -new -key $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -subj /CN=$username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_csr"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Creation & Signing"
        user_cert=$(sudo openssl x509 -req -in $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -CA /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.crt -CAkey /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt -days $validity 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_cert"
        echo " "
echo "Ubuntu User Account \"$username\" mapping with generated certificate & key"
        user_cred_set=$(sudo kubectl config set-credentials $username --client-certificate=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt --client-key=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2&gt;&1)
        user_cred_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |grep -A50 users:|grep -A0 $username)
        echo "$user_cred_set"
        echo "$username Mappings:"
        echo "$user_cred_verify"
        echo " "
echo "Context setup for  $username : "
        user_context=$(sudo kubectl config set-context $username --cluster=kubernetes --namespace=$username --user=$username 2&gt;&1)
        user_context_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |awk ''/context:/,/current-context:/''|grep -B4 "name: $username")
        echo "$user_context"
        echo "$username Context:"
        echo "$user_context_verify"
        echo "Files Created during the operation:"

cd $username
dir

}


#=====================================Kubernetes Roles Creation======================================================================


roles_creation()

{

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd  $HOME/.RBAC
mkdir $username
cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: OnlyJobs
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods","pods/log"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch"]
- apiGroups: ["batch","extensions"]
  resources: ["jobs"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch","create","update","patch","delete"]
EOF




cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: owner
rules:
- apiGroups: ["*"]
  resources: ["*"]
  verbs: ["*"]
EOF


cd $HOME/.RBAC/$username

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml

echo "Roles Created :"
user_role1=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep owner)
user_role2=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep OnlyJobs)
echo "User Role 1 - $user_role1"
echo "User Role 2 - $user_role2"

echo "Roles .yaml file are generated during operations:"
dir
}

#===================================Kubernetes Role Bindings Creation===========================================================

rolebinding_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role Binding creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-RoleBinding.yaml
kind: RoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: $username
  namespace: $username
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: $username
  apiGroup: ""
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: owner
  apiGroup: ""

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/$username-RoleBinding.yaml
echo "Role Binding Operation:"
user_rolebinding=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings   --all-namespaces    -o custom-columns=''KIND:kind,NAMESPACE:metadata.namespace,NAME:metadata.name,SERVICE_ACCOUNTS:subjects[?(@.kind=="ServiceAccount")].name''|grep "$username" 2&gt;&1)
echo "$user_rolebinding"

echo "Role binding file generated during operation"
dir
}

#==================================User Configuration File Generation===============================

create_config_file()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== User Configuration file Generation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd /etc/kubernetes/

sudo sed -n ''1,9 p'' admin.conf &gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config

cat &lt;&lt;EOT &gt;&gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config
    namespace: $username
    user: $username
  name: $username
current-context: $username
kind: Config
preferences: {}
users:
- name: $username
  user:
    client-certificate: $username.crt
    client-key: $username.key
EOT

echo " Config File Generated"
user_config_file=$(cat $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config)
echo "$user_config_file"



}



#====================================================Authentication Files - Provisioning to User=========-======

copy_authentication_files()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Authentication Files - Provisioning to User Setup - Started"
echo " "
		sudo chmod -R 755 /home/$username
        cd /
        cd /home/$username
        pwd
        sudo mkdir .kube
        sudo cp $HOME/.certs/$username/* /home/$username/.kube
        sudo rm /home/$username/.kube/$username.csr
        sudo cp /home/$username/.kube/$username.config /home/$username/.kube/config
        sudo cp /home/jarvis/pod_creation.sh .
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/*
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/.kube
        sudo chown -R $username:$username /home/$username/.kube/*
        cd .kube
        ls -a
echo "Authentication File Transfered:"

}



#========================================Setting Kube Config File=====================================



set_kubeconfig()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Kube Config File Setup - Started"
echo " "

echo "sudo export KUBECONFIG=/home/$username/.k8s-authentication/$username.config" #&gt;&gt; /home/$username/.bashrc

echo "Kube Config  file set"

}


#=====================================Setting Resource quota===========================================

set_quota()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting Resource Quota Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: compute-resource
spec:
  hard:
    requests.nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
EOF

echo "Quota has been set"

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl create -f $HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml --namespace=$username

user_quota=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl describe namespace $username)
echo "$user_quota"
}

username=@p1
upload_status="@p2"
if [ "$upload_status" = "1" ]
then
cp -r /mnt/nfs_share/upload/@p4 /mnt/nfs_share/home/$username
fi

image="@p3"
echo $image
gpu=@gpu
echo $gpu

apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: Job
metadata:
  name: $job_name
spec:
  backoffLimit: 0
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: $job_name
          image: $image
          command: ["python"]
          args: ["/workspace/$filename"]
          resources:
            requests:
              memory: "@ramGi"
              cpu: "@cpum"
              nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
            limits:
              memory: "@ramGi"
              cpu: "@cpum"
              nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
          volumeMounts:
          - name: jarvis
            mountPath: /workspace
      volumes:
      - name: jarvis
        hostPath:
          path: $filepath
          type: Directory
      restartPolicy: Never

EOF
cd $filepath
echo | kubectl create -f $filepath/job.yaml
rm job.yaml', N'Update on 4 August By Aditya', 0, 5, 1, 1, CAST(N'2020-09-04T21:23:12.387' AS DateTime))

setting_up_file_permissions()

#=====================================Command to create users on Compute Nodes====================================

nodeuser_creation()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Command to create user on compute node section - Started"
echo " "

userid=$(sudo id $username)
user_id=$(echo $userid | awk ''{print substr($0,5,4)}'')
echo "UID of $username - $user_id"
nodeuser="sudo useradd -u $user_id -m -d /userdata/$username -s /bin/bash -c \"$displayname\" $username"
echo "Command for Compute nodes:"
echo $nodeuser
echo "[{\"computenodecommand\":\"$nodeuser\"}]"
}


#-m  Craeting home directory as /$HOME/$username
#-d  Giving a different path to home directory
#-s  To specify a default shell
#-c  To  provide a comment
#sudo useradd -m -d /opt/username username
#sudo useradd -u 1500 username
#sudo useradd -g users username

#========================================Kubernetes Credential Setup======================================================================

credential_creation()
 {

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Credential Setup - Started"
echo " "

        cd $HOME/.certs

        mkdir $username
echo "Namespace Creation"
        sudo kubectl create namespace $username
        user_ns=$(sudo kubectl  get namespace $username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "User Namespace:"
        echo "$user_ns"
        echo " "
echo "Key Generation"
        user_key=$(sudo openssl genrsa -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2048 2&lt;&1)
        echo "$user_key"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Signing Request Generation"
        user_csr=$(sudo openssl req -new -key $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -subj /CN=$username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_csr"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Creation & Signing"
        user_cert=$(sudo openssl x509 -req -in $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -CA /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.crt -CAkey /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt -days $validity 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_cert"
        echo " "
echo "Ubuntu User Account \"$username\" mapping with generated certificate & key"
        user_cred_set=$(sudo kubectl config set-credentials $username --client-certificate=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt --client-key=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2&gt;&1)
        user_cred_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |grep -A50 users:|grep -A0 $username)
        echo "$user_cred_set"
        echo "$username Mappings:"
        echo "$user_cred_verify"
        echo " "
echo "Context setup for  $username : "
        user_context=$(sudo kubectl config set-context $username --cluster=kubernetes --namespace=$username --user=$username 2&gt;&1)
        user_context_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |awk ''/context:/,/current-context:/''|grep -B4 "name: $username")
        echo "$user_context"
        echo "$username Context:"
        echo "$user_context_verify"
        echo "Files Created during the operation:"

cd $username
dir

}


#=====================================Kubernetes Roles Creation======================================================================


roles_creation()

{

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd  $HOME/.RBAC
mkdir $username
cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: OnlyJobs
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods","pods/log"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch"]
- apiGroups: ["batch","extensions"]
  resources: ["jobs"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch","create","update","patch","delete"]
EOF




cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: owner
rules:
- apiGroups: ["*"]
  resources: ["*"]
  verbs: ["*"]
EOF


cd $HOME/.RBAC/$username

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml

echo "Roles Created :"
user_role1=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep owner)
user_role2=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep OnlyJobs)
echo "User Role 1 - $user_role1"
echo "User Role 2 - $user_role2"

echo "Roles .yaml file are generated during operations:"
dir
}

#===================================Kubernetes Role Bindings Creation===========================================================

rolebinding_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role Binding creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-RoleBinding.yaml
kind: RoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: $username
  namespace: $username
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: $username
  apiGroup: ""
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: owner
  apiGroup: ""

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/$username-RoleBinding.yaml
echo "Role Binding Operation:"
user_rolebinding=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings   --all-namespaces    -o custom-columns=''KIND:kind,NAMESPACE:metadata.namespace,NAME:metadata.name,SERVICE_ACCOUNTS:subjects[?(@.kind=="ServiceAccount")].name''|grep "$username" 2&gt;&1)
echo "$user_rolebinding"

echo "Role binding file generated during operation"
dir
}

#==================================User Configuration File Generation===============================

create_config_file()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== User Configuration file Generation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd /etc/kubernetes/

sudo sed -n ''1,9 p'' admin.conf &gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config

cat &lt;&lt;EOT &gt;&gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config
    namespace: $username
    user: $username
  name: $username
current-context: $username
kind: Config
preferences: {}
users:
- name: $username
  user:
    client-certificate: $username.crt
    client-key: $username.key
EOT

echo " Config File Generated"
user_config_file=$(cat $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config)
echo "$user_config_file"



}



#====================================================Authentication Files - Provisioning to User=========-======

copy_authentication_files()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Authentication Files - Provisioning to User Setup - Started"
echo " "
		sudo chmod -R 755 "${homepath}${username}"
        cd /
        cd "${homepath}${username}"
        pwd
        sudo mkdir .kube
        sudo cp $HOME/.certs/$username/* "${homepath}${username}"/.kube
       # sudo rm /home/$username/.kube/$username.csr 
        sudo cp "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/$username.config "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/config
        sudo cp /home/jarvis/pod_creation.sh .
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/*
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/.kube
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/*
        cd .kube
        ls -a
echo "Authentication File Transfered:"

}

#=====================================Setting Resource quota===========================================

set_quota()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting Resource Quota Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: compute-resource
spec:
  hard:
    requests.nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
EOF

echo "Quota has been set"

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl create -f $HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml --namespace=$username

user_quota=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl describe namespace $username)
echo "$user_quota"
}

    nodePort:

    targetPort: 8888

        echo "$user_csr"

- name: $username
  user:
    client-certificate: $username.crt
    client-key: $username.key
EOT

echo " Config File Generated"
user_config_file=$(cat $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config)
echo "$user_config_file"



}



#====================================================Authentication Files - Provisioning to User=========-======

copy_authentication_files()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Authentication Files - Provisioning to User Setup - Started"
echo " "
		sudo chmod -R 755 "${homepath}${username}"
        cd /
        cd "${homepath}${username}"
        pwd
        sudo mkdir .kube
        sudo cp $HOME/.certs/$username/* "${homepath}${username}"/.kube
       # sudo rm /home/$username/.kube/$username.csr 
        sudo cp "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/$username.config "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/config
        sudo cp /home/jarvis/pod_creation.sh .
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/*
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/.kube
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/*
        cd .kube
        ls -a
echo "Authentication File Transfered:"

}



#========================================Setting Kube Config File=====================================



set_kubeconfig()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Kube Config File Setup - Started"
echo " "

echo "sudo export KUBECONFIG=/home/$username/.k8s-authentication/$username.config" #&gt;&gt; /home/$username/.bashrc

echo "Kube Config  file set"

}


#=====================================Setting Resource quota===========================================

set_quota()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting Resource Quota Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: compute-resource
spec:
  hard:
    requests.cpu: $cpu
    requests.memory: $memory
    limits.cpu: $cpu
    limits.memory: $memory
    requests.nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
    pods: $pods

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl create -f $HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml --namespace=$username

echo "Quota has been set"

user_quota=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl describe namespace $username)
echo "$user_quota"
}

set_kubeconfig

nodeuser_creation', N'', 0, 5, 1, 1, CAST(N'2020-08-25T16:33:16.707' AS DateTime))

# Create $HOME/.certs
# Create $HOME/.RBAC/
#=========================================Variable Declarations=============================
echo " "
echo "==============================Variable Declaration Section  - started"
echo " "
username="@p1"
#deluser $username
#rm -R /home/$username
password="@p2"

setting_up_ubuntu_user()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Setting up ububtu user - Started"
echo " "

sudo useradd -p $(openssl passwd -1 $password) -m -s /bin/bash -d "${homepath}" $username
echo "user created"

#user=$(sudo useradd -m -d /home/$username -s /bin/bash -c "$displayname " $username 2&gt;&1)
#echo "$user"
#echo admin123 | sudo -S echo -e  "$password\n$password\n" |passwd $username
#echo "password changed"
u_confirm="$(sudo id $username)"
echo "$username - UID & GID:"
echo $u_confirm

user_len=${#username}
echo $user_len
user_new=$(echo $u_confirm |awk ''{ print substr($0,10,$user_len)}'')
echo $user_new
user_test=0
if [ "$user_new" == "$username" ] ;
then
user_test=1
fi
echo "User Creation Test = $user_test"

}

#==============================Setting up Permissions on USER directory============================

setting_up_file_permissions()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting File Permission on user home directory - Started"
echo " "

sudo chown -R $username:$username ${homepath}${username}
sudo chmod -R 755 ${homepath}${username}
echo "Permissions on Home Directory:"
echo " "
cd ${homepath}

user_hm=$(sudo ls $username -l)
echo $user_hm
echo " "


hmdir_test=0
user_hmdir=$(echo user_hm | grep $username |awk ''{print $1}'')
if [ "$user_hmdir" == "drwxr-xr-x" ];
then
hmdir_test=1
fi
echo "Home Directory Test = $hmdir_test" 
}


#=====================================Command to create users on Compute Nodes====================================

nodeuser_creation()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Command to create user on compute node section - Started"
echo " "

userid=$(sudo id $username)
user_id=$(echo $userid | awk ''{print substr($0,5,4)}'')
echo "UID of $username - $user_id"
nodeuser="sudo useradd -u $user_id -m -d /userdata/$username -s /bin/bash -c \''$displayname\'' $username"
echo "Command for Compute nodes:"
echo $nodeuser
echo "[{\"computenodecommand\":\"$nodeuser\"}]"
}


#-m  Craeting home directory as /$HOME/$username
#-d  Giving a different path to home directory
#-s  To specify a default shell
#-c  To  provide a comment
#sudo useradd -m -d /opt/username username
#sudo useradd -u 1500 username
#sudo useradd -g users username

#========================================Kubernetes Credential Setup======================================================================

credential_creation()
 {

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Credential Setup - Started"
echo " "

        cd $HOME/.certs

        mkdir $username
echo "Namespace Creation"
        sudo kubectl create namespace $username
        user_ns=$(sudo kubectl  get namespace $username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "User Namespace:"
        echo "$user_ns"
        echo " "
echo "Key Generation"
        user_key=$(sudo openssl genrsa -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2048 2&lt;&1)
        echo "$user_key"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Signing Request Generation"
        user_csr=$(sudo openssl req -new -key $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -subj /CN=$username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_csr"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Creation & Signing"
        user_cert=$(sudo openssl x509 -req -in $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -CA /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.crt -CAkey /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt -days $validity 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_cert"
        echo " "
echo "Ubuntu User Account \"$username\" mapping with generated certificate & key"
        user_cred_set=$(sudo kubectl config set-credentials $username --client-certificate=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt --client-key=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2&gt;&1)
        user_cred_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |grep -A50 users:|grep -A0 $username)
        echo "$user_cred_set"
        echo "$username Mappings:"
        echo "$user_cred_verify"
        echo " "
echo "Context setup for  $username : "
        user_context=$(sudo kubectl config set-context $username --cluster=kubernetes --namespace=$username --user=$username 2&gt;&1)
        user_context_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |awk ''/context:/,/current-context:/''|grep -B4 "name: $username")
        echo "$user_context"
        echo "$username Context:"
        echo "$user_context_verify"
        echo "Files Created during the operation:"

cd $username
dir

}


#=====================================Kubernetes Roles Creation======================================================================


roles_creation()

{

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd  $HOME/.RBAC
mkdir $username
cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: OnlyJobs
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods","pods/log"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch"]
- apiGroups: ["batch","extensions"]
  resources: ["jobs"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch","create","update","patch","delete"]
EOF




cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: owner
rules:
- apiGroups: ["*"]
  resources: ["*"]
  verbs: ["*"]
EOF


cd $HOME/.RBAC/$username

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml

echo "Roles Created :"
user_role1=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep owner)
user_role2=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep OnlyJobs)
echo "User Role 1 - $user_role1"
echo "User Role 2 - $user_role2"

echo "Roles .yaml file are generated during operations:"
dir
}

#===================================Kubernetes Role Bindings Creation===========================================================

rolebinding_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role Binding creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-RoleBinding.yaml
kind: RoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1beta1
metadata:
  name: $username
  namespace: $username
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: $username
  apiGroup: ""
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: owner
  apiGroup: ""

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/$username-RoleBinding.yaml
echo "Role Binding Operation:"
user_rolebinding=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings   --all-namespaces    -o custom-columns=''KIND:kind,NAMESPACE:metadata.namespace,NAME:metadata.name,SERVICE_ACCOUNTS:subjects[?(@.kind=="ServiceAccount")].name''|grep "$username" 2&gt;&1)
echo "$user_rolebinding"

echo "Role binding file generated during operation"
dir
}

#==================================User Configuration File Generation===============================

create_config_file()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== User Configuration file Generation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd /etc/kubernetes/

sudo sed -n ''1,9 p'' admin.conf &gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config

cat &lt;&lt;EOT &gt;&gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config
    namespace: $username
    user: $username
  name: $username
current-context: $username
kind: Config
preferences: {}
users:
- name: $username
  user:
    client-certificate: $username.crt
    client-key: $username.key
EOT

echo " Config File Generated"
user_config_file=$(cat $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config)
echo "$user_config_file"



}



#====================================================Authentication Files - Provisioning to User=========-======

copy_authentication_files()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Authentication Files - Provisioning to User Setup - Started"
echo " "
		sudo chmod -R 755 "${homepath}${username}"
        cd /
        cd "${homepath}${username}"
        pwd
        sudo mkdir .kube
        sudo cp $HOME/.certs/$username/* "${homepath}${username}"/.kube
       # sudo rm /home/$username/.kube/$username.csr 
        sudo cp "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/$username.config "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/config
        sudo cp /home/jarvis/pod_creation.sh .
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/*
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/.kube
        sudo chown -R $username:$username "${homepath}${username}"/.kube/*
        cd .kube
        ls -a
echo "Authentication File Transfered:"

}

#=====================================Setting Resource quota===========================================

set_quota()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting Resource Quota Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: compute-resource
spec:
  hard:
    requests.cpu: $cpu
    requests.memory: $memory
    limits.cpu: $cpu
    limits.memory: $memory
    requests.nvidia.com/gpu: $gpu
    pods: $pods

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl create -f $HOME/.RBAC/${username}-quota.yaml --namespace=$username

echo "Quota has been set"

user_quota=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl describe namespace $username)
echo "$user_quota"
}

setting_up_ubuntu_user()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Setting up ububtu user - Started"
echo " "

sudo useradd -p $(openssl passwd -1 $password) -m -s /bin/bash -d "${homepath}${username}" $username
echo "user created"

#echo admin123 | sudo -S echo -e  "$password\n$password\n" |passwd $username
#echo "password changed"
u_confirm="$(sudo id $username)"
echo "$username - UID & GID:"
echo $u_confirm

user_len=${#username}
echo $user_len
user_new=$(echo $u_confirm |awk ''{ print substr($0,10,$user_len)}'')
echo $user_new
user_test=0
if [ "$user_new" == "$username" ] ;
then
user_test=1
fi
echo "User Creation Test = $user_test"

}

#==============================Setting up Permissions on USER directory============================

setting_up_file_permissions()

{
echo " "
echo "==============================  Setting File Permission on user home directory - Started"
echo " "

sudo chown -R $username:$username ${homepath}${username}
sudo chmod -R 755 ${homepath}${username}
echo "Permissions on Home Directory:"
echo " "
cd ${homepath}

user_hm=$(sudo ls $username -l)
echo $user_hm
echo " "


hmdir_test=0
user_hmdir=$(echo user_hm | grep $username |awk ''{print $1}'')
if [ "$user_hmdir" == "drwxr-xr-x" ];
then
hmdir_test=1
fi
echo "Home Directory Test = $hmdir_test" 
}


#=====================================Command to create users on Compute Nodes====================================

nodeuser_creation()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== Command to create user on compute node section - Started"
echo " "

userid=$(sudo id $username)
user_id=$(echo $userid | awk ''{print substr($0,5,4)}'')
echo "UID of $username - $user_id"
nodeuser="sudo useradd -u $user_id -m -d /userdata/$username -s /bin/bash -c \''$displayname\'' $username"
echo "Command for Compute nodes:"
echo $nodeuser
echo "[{\"computenodecommand\":\"$nodeuser\"}]"
}


#-m  Craeting home directory as /$HOME/$username
#-d  Giving a different path to home directory
#-s  To specify a default shell
#-c  To  provide a comment
#sudo useradd -m -d /opt/username username
#sudo useradd -u 1500 username
#sudo useradd -g users username

#========================================Kubernetes Credential Setup======================================================================

credential_creation()
 {

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Credential Setup - Started"
echo " "

        cd $HOME/.certs

        mkdir $username
echo "Namespace Creation"
        sudo kubectl create namespace $username
        user_ns=$(sudo kubectl  get namespace $username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "User Namespace:"
        echo "$user_ns"
        echo " "
echo "Key Generation"
        user_key=$(sudo openssl genrsa -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2048 2&lt;&1)
        echo "$user_key"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Signing Request Generation"
        user_csr=$(sudo openssl req -new -key $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -subj /CN=$username 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_csr"
#sleep 5
        echo " "
echo "Certificate Creation & Signing"
        user_cert=$(sudo openssl x509 -req -in $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.csr -CA /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.crt -CAkey /etc/kubernetes/pki/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt -days $validity 2&gt;&1)
        echo "$user_cert"
        echo " "
echo "Ubuntu User Account \"$username\" mapping with generated certificate & key"
        user_cred_set=$(sudo kubectl config set-credentials $username --client-certificate=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.crt --client-key=$HOME/.certs/$username/$username.key 2&gt;&1)
        user_cred_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |grep -A50 users:|grep -A0 $username)
        echo "$user_cred_set"
        echo "$username Mappings:"
        echo "$user_cred_verify"
        echo " "
echo "Context setup for  $username : "
        user_context=$(sudo kubectl config set-context $username --cluster=kubernetes --namespace=$username --user=$username 2&gt;&1)
        user_context_verify=$(sudo kubectl config view |awk ''/context:/,/current-context:/''|grep -B4 "name: $username")
        echo "$user_context"
        echo "$username Context:"
        echo "$user_context_verify"
        echo "Files Created during the operation:"

cd $username
dir

}


#=====================================Kubernetes Roles Creation======================================================================


roles_creation()

{

echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd  $HOME/.RBAC
mkdir $username
cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: OnlyJobs
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods","pods/log"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch"]
- apiGroups: ["batch","extensions"]
  resources: ["jobs"]
  verbs: ["get","list","watch","create","update","patch","delete"]
EOF




cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: owner
rules:
- apiGroups: ["*"]
  resources: ["*"]
  verbs: ["*"]
EOF


cd $HOME/.RBAC/$username

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-pod_role.yaml
echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-job_role.yaml

echo "Roles Created :"
user_role1=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep owner)
user_role2=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get clusterroles|grep OnlyJobs)
echo "User Role 1 - $user_role1"
echo "User Role 2 - $user_role2"

echo "Roles .yaml file are generated during operations:"
dir
}

#===================================Kubernetes Role Bindings Creation===========================================================

rolebinding_creation()

{
echo " "
echo "============================== Kubernetes Role Binding creation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cat &lt;&lt;EOF &gt;$HOME/.RBAC/$username/${username}-RoleBinding.yaml
kind: RoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: $username
  namespace: $username
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: $username
  apiGroup: ""
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: owner
  apiGroup: ""

EOF

echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl apply -f $HOME/.RBAC/$username/$username-RoleBinding.yaml
echo "Role Binding Operation:"
user_rolebinding=$(echo admin123 | sudo -S kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings   --all-namespaces    -o custom-columns=''KIND:kind,NAMESPACE:metadata.namespace,NAME:metadata.name,SERVICE_ACCOUNTS:subjects[?(@.kind=="ServiceAccount")].name''|grep "$username" 2&gt;&1)
echo "$user_rolebinding"

echo "Role binding file generated during operation"
dir
}

#==================================User Configuration File Generation===============================

create_config_file()
{
echo " "
echo "============================== User Configuration file Generation Setup - Started"
echo " "

cd /etc/kubernetes/

sudo sed -n ''1,9 p'' admin.conf &gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config

cat &lt;&lt;EOT &gt;&gt; $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config
    namespace: $username
    user: $username
  name: $username
current-context: $username
kind: Config
preferences: {}
users:
- name: $username
  user:
    client-certificate: $username.crt
    client-key: $username.key
EOT

echo " Config File Generated"
user_config_file=$(cat $HOME/.certs/$username/$username.config)
echo "$user_config_file"



}

Sets a user entry in kubeconfig

 Specifying a name that already exists will merge new fields on top of existing values.

  Client-certificate flags:
  --client-certificate=certfile --client-key=keyfile
  
  Bearer token flags:
    --token=bearer_token
  
  Basic auth flags:
    --username=basic_user --password=basic_password
  
 Bearer token and basic auth are mutually exclusive.

Examples:
  # Set only the "client-key" field on the "cluster-admin"
  # entry, without touching other values:
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --client-key=~/.kube/admin.key
  
  # Set basic auth for the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --username=admin --password=uXFGweU9l35qcif
  
  # Embed client certificate data in the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --client-certificate=~/.kube/admin.crt --embed-certs=true
  
  # Enable the Google Compute Platform auth provider for the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --auth-provider=gcp
  
  # Enable the OpenID Connect auth provider for the "cluster-admin" entry with additional args
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --auth-provider=oidc --auth-provider-arg=client-id=foo --auth-provider-arg=client-secret=bar
  
  # Remove the "client-secret" config value for the OpenID Connect auth provider for the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --auth-provider=oidc --auth-provider-arg=client-secret-
  
  # Enable new exec auth plugin for the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --exec-command=/path/to/the/executable --exec-api-version=client.authentication.k8s.io/v1beta1
  
  # Define new exec auth plugin args for the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --exec-arg=arg1 --exec-arg=arg2
  
  # Create or update exec auth plugin environment variables for the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --exec-env=key1=val1 --exec-env=key2=val2
  
  # Remove exec auth plugin environment variables for the "cluster-admin" entry
  kubectl config set-credentials cluster-admin --exec-env=var-to-remove-

Options:
      --auth-provider='''': Auth provider for the user entry in kubeconfig
      --auth-provider-arg=[]: ''key=value'' arguments for the auth provider
      --embed-certs=false: Embed client cert/key for the user entry in kubeconfig
      --exec-api-version='''': API version of the exec credential plugin for the user entry in kubeconfig
      --exec-arg=[]: New arguments for the exec credential plugin command for the user entry in kubeconfig
      --exec-command='''': Command for the exec credential plugin for the user entry in kubeconfig
      --exec-env=[]: ''key=value'' environment values for the exec credential plugin

Usage:
  kubectl config set-credentials NAME [--client-certificate=path/to/certfile] [--client-key=path/to/keyfile] [--token=bearer_token] [--username=basic_user] [--password=basic_password] [--auth-provider=provider_name] [--auth-provider-arg=key=value] [--exec-command=exec_command] [--exec-api-version=exec_api_version] [--exec-arg=arg] [--exec-env=key=value] [options]

INSERT [dbo].[tblbackup_jobscript] ([id], [report_script]) VALUES (NULL, N'job_info=($(kubectl get jobs -o wide --all-namespaces |awk -vi="@i" ''NR==i{print $0}''))

echo "{"
echo "\"user_name\" : \"${job_info[0]}\","
echo "\"ns_name\" : \"${job_info[0]}\","
echo "\"job_name\" : \"${job_info[1]}\","
echo "\"completions\" : \"${job_info[2]}\","
echo "\"duration\" : \"${job_info[3]}\","
echo "\"age\" : \"${job_info[4]}\","
echo "\"containers\" : \"${job_info[5]}\","
echo "\"images\" : \"${job_info[6]}\","
echo "\"selector\" : \"${job_info[7]}\","

job_name=$(echo ${job_info[1]})
job_start_info=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==9{ print $0}''))
echo "\"job_start_day\" : \"${job_start_info[2]}\","
echo "\"job_start_month\" : \"${job_start_info[3]}\","
echo "\"job_start_year\" : \"${job_start_info[4]}\","
echo "\"job__start_time\" : \"${job_start_info[6]}\","
job_start_info=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==10{ print $0}''))
echo "\"job_end_day\" : \"${job_start_info[2]}\","
echo "\"job_end_month\" : \"${job_start_info[3]}\","
echo "\"job_end_year\" : \"${job_start_info[4]}\","
echo "\"job_end_time\" : \"${job_start_info[6]}\","
job_file_info=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==24{ print substr($1,12.$NR)}''))
echo "\"job_file\" : \"$job_file_info\","
job_file_path=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==33{print $2}''))
echo "\"job_file_path\" : \"$job_file_path\""
echo "}"')
INSERT [dbo].[tblbackup_jobscript] ([id], [report_script]) VALUES (NULL, N'job_info=($(kubectl get jobs -o wide --all-namespaces |awk -vi="2" ''NR==i{print $0}''))

echo "{"
echo "\"user_name\" : \"${job_info[0]}\","
echo "\"ns_name\" : \"${job_info[0]}\","
echo "\"job_name\" : \"${job_info[1]}\","
echo "\"completions\" : \"${job_info[2]}\","
echo "\"duration\" : \"${job_info[3]}\","
echo "\"age\" : \"${job_info[4]}\","
echo "\"containers\" : \"${job_info[5]}\","
echo "\"images\" : \"${job_info[6]}\","
echo "\"selector\" : \"${job_info[7]}\","

job_name=$(echo ${job_info[1]})
output=$(kubectl get pods | grep $job_name)
status=$(echo $output | awk ''{print $1 " " $3}'')
job_start_info=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==9{ print $0}''))
echo "\"job_start_day\" : \"${job_start_info[2]}\","
echo "\"job_start_month\" : \"${job_start_info[3]}\","
echo "\"job_start_year\" : \"${job_start_info[4]}\","
echo "\"job__start_time\" : \"${job_start_info[6]}\","
job_start_info=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==10{ print $0}''))
echo "\"job_end_day\" : \"${job_start_info[2]}\","
echo "\"job_end_month\" : \"${job_start_info[3]}\","
echo "\"job_end_year\" : \"${job_start_info[4]}\","
echo "\"job_end_time\" : \"${job_start_info[6]}\","
job_file_info=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==24{ print substr($1,12.$NR)}''))
echo "\"job_file\" : \"$job_file_info\","
job_file_path=($(kubectl describe job $job_name |awk ''NR==33{print $2}''))
echo "\"job_file_path\" : \"$job_file_path\""
echo "\"status is\":\"$status\""
echo "}"')

INSERT [dbo].[tblbackup_jobscript] ([id], [report_script]) VALUES (NULL, N'job_info=($(kubectl get jobs -o wide --all-namespaces |awk -vi="4" ''NR==i{print $0}''))

echo "{"
echo "\"user_name\" : \"${job_info[0]}\","
echo "\"ns_name\" : \"${job_info[0]}\","
echo "\"job_name\" : \"${job_info[1]}\","
echo "\"completions\" : \"${job_info[2]}\","
echo "\"duration\" : \"${job_info[3]}\","
echo "\"age\" : \"${job_info[4]}\","
echo "\"containers\" : \"${job_info[5]}\","
echo "\"images\" : \"${job_info[6]}\","
echo "\"selector\" : \"${job_info[7]}\","

job_name=$(echo ${job_info[1]})
output=$(kubectl get pods  -n ${job_info[0]} | grep $job_name)
status=$(echo $output | awk ''{print $1 " " $3}'')
job_start_info=($(kubectl describe job -n ${job_info[0]} $job_name |awk ''NR==9{ print $0}''))
echo "\"job_start_day\" : \"${job_start_info[2]}\","
echo "\"job_start_month\" : \"${job_start_info[3]}\","
echo "\"job_start_year\" : \"${job_start_info[4]}\","
echo "\"job__start_time\" : \"${job_start_info[6]}\","
job_start_info=($(kubectl describe job -n ${job_info[0]} $job_name |awk ''NR==10{ print $0}''))
echo "\"job_end_day\" : \"${job_start_info[2]}\","
echo "\"status\":\"$status\","
echo "\"job_end_month\" : \"${job_start_info[3]}\","
echo "\"job_end_year\" : \"${job_start_info[4]}\","
echo "\"job_end_time\" : \"${job_start_info[6]}\","
job_file_info=($(kubectl describe job -n ${job_info[0]} $job_name |awk ''NR==24{ print substr($1,12.$NR)}''))
echo "\"job_file\" : \"$job_file_info\","
job_file_path=($(kubectl describe job -n ${job_info[0]} $job_name |awk ''NR==33{print $2}''))
echo "\"job_file_path\" : \"$job_file_path\""

echo "}"')
ALTER TABLE [dbo].[m_department] ADD  CONSTRAINT [DF_m_department_dept_del_status]  DEFAULT ((1)) FOR [dept_del_status]
GO
